works.description: Commissioned by American financier, banker and art collector J.P. Morgan in 1890, the 241-foot “Corsair II” megayacht had been host to some of the influential men of that time, including Theodore Roosevelt, William Taft, George Westinghouse, Henry Ford, John D. Rockefeller, Andrew Carnegie, Mark Twain and light bulb inventor Thomas Edison. Although the Corsair II was decommissioned and scrapped long back, the items from the yacht that speak well of J.P. Morgan’s high life at sea will be hitting the auction block this Sunday in Boston.
